            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.113-114_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">113</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">TWEEDSMUIR,
                        <lb/>
                        KANAWHA FALLS,
                            <lb/>
                            WEST VIRGINIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear Doctor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The Danish nurse who cared for me on my holiday abroad this summer is with us for a few months, in residence at Kanawha Falls. It interests me greatly that she keeps a copy of your Collected Poems on her bedside table. Already she has memorized many of the more serious short poems, and generous passages from the long ones. You have never had a more eager disciple.</p>
                
                <p>Now I am venturing to ask you for a great favor. Only our long friendship emboldens me to go so far. Will you please write her a brief letter, with a handwritten copy of one of the poems? Passages from the Witless Musician would be especially appropriate.</p>
                
                <p>This would make her very happy and also confirm her in a noble resolution she has made. Her headquarters when she returns to Europe will be in Paris, where she has numerous friends and acquaintances among people well placed in the social order. She is going to spread the knowledge of your outstanding work as faithfully and effectively as Doctor House and Doctor Vining ever did. So you see why I am so eager.</p>
                
                <p>The holiday abroad was most pleasant. Mrs. Laird seems a bit improved. We speak of you often and wish you well. Doctor Vining joins me in salutations. May all good things be yours.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Mizpah!</salute>
                
                    <salute>Shalom aleichem.</salute>
                    <signed>William R. Laird</signed>
                    <signed>William R. Laird</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <dateline>20 June 1958</dateline>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi>:</opener> <p>The address is Miss Birgit Svendsen, Kanawha Falls, West Virginia.</p>
                </postscript>
                
